                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_calx" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>calx</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>колесо</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>wheel</q></abv:tr></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>calxy ḱʼīl</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">обод колеса</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">wheel rim</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>calxy dændag</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">спица</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">radius</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („зуб колеса“)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (wheel tooth)</note></abv:example><abv:example><quote>calxy mæskʼ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">ступица</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">hob</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>k˳yrojy calx</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">мельничная турбина</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">mill's wheel</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>Ojnoni calx Soslani marunmæ ærcudæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>колесо Ойнона пришло убить Сослана</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>Ojnon's wheel came to kill Soslan</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 19</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>mæj jæ calxy ʒag ū</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>луна находится в фазе полнолуния („в полное колесо“)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the moon is in the full moon phase ("full wheel")</q></abv:tr></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Общее индоевропейское слово. Исходная древнеиранская форма — <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*čaxra-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>čark</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>carx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*čaxr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*čarx-(čγrh, črγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>čaxra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>čakra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>κύκλος</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/> <w>hweohl</w></mentioned>, без удвоения начального согласного — <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>коло</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>колесо</w></mentioned>. Широко распространилось (под влиянием персидского, а возможно и скифо-аланского) в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/> <w>čʼaxr</w> <gloss><q>вращение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w>čaxarak</w> <gloss><q>прялка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>čarxi</w> <gloss><q>станок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>čʼarxa</w> <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><w/> <gloss><q>часть ткацкого станка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>точило</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ani"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/> <w>čark</w> <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><w/> <gloss><q>сфера</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для объяснения %iI%i в %icalx%i приходится исходить из производной формы *%ičaxrya%i- (%iг%i перед %iy%i → %il%i). Ср. другие слова из круга ‘колесо—колесница’: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdon"/> ‘арба’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rætænaǧd"/> ‘оглобля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘оглобля’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 78, III 159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I 54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A common Indo-European word. The initial Old Iranian form is <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*čaxra-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>čark</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>carx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*čaxr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*čarx-(čγrh, črγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>čaxra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>čakra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>κύκλος</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/> <w>hweohl</w></mentioned>, without doubling of the initial consonant — <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>kolo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>koleso</w></mentioned>. The word is widespread in Caucasian languages (under the influence of Persian and probably Scythian-Alan): <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/> <w>čʼaxr</w> <gloss><q>rotation</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w>čaxarakʼ</w> <gloss><q>spinning-wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>čarxi</w> <gloss><q>lathe</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>čʼarxa</w> <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><w/> <gloss><q>part of a weaver loom</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>grindstone</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ani"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>čarx</w> <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Also here <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/> <w>čark</w> <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><w/> <gloss><q>sphere</q></gloss></mentioned>. To explain %iI%i in %icalx%i we have to assume a derivated from *%ičaxrya%i- (%iг%i before %iy%i → %il%i). Cf. other words in the field ‘wheel—chariot’: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdon"/> ‘bullock-cart’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rætænaǧd"/> ‘shaft’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘shaft’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 78, III 159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I 54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>